rComments: The worst professor that I've had the displeasure of having during my time at UOttawa. Made the exam extremely hard even though he kept telling us that it's going to be easy. He made the course insanely difficult especially since this is supposedly a "bird course".

Terrible professor. Made the exams insanely difficult with not enough time to complete it. This course was supposed to be an "easy" first year course but he made it more difficult than any other math course that I have taken. Avoid him.

Kind Professor.He is very concerned about his students. He replied to e-mail very quickly.He is willing to help 
 students get good grade.Most importantly, he has no accent.

Professor Cebanu is very caring and provides clear lectures. he is good at answering questions and making sure all students understand. he posts all lectures and provides fill in notes as well as the filled in version of the notes.

Professor Radu does a great job teaching. He goes over stuff carefully and shows some proofs to help you understand. Sometimes he can be a bit confusing, but if you ask he will explain more. Very funny in class too.
He was a great prof during the pandemic. When many students bombed the first midterm, he adjusted the course deliverables to help.
bad
Good prof i just suck at linear algebra

Genuinely a great guy. He cares about his students and the work is graded quite easily throughout the course. He has a lot of patience and will repeat himself a million times if he has to during lectures. Our first midterm was hard but after that he gave everyone an opportunity to better their grade. Aside from that, work was fair. Do the homework.

I think this prof is fair. There are 2 midterms and 1 final in this class. We have midterm 1 on Oct.14th. I have to admit that midterm 1 is difficult. After the mark is out. The average score is a bit low, so he makes an option test which is done at home. Others are fine. His textbook's link is in the syllabus and is free( but I rarely assess it).

He is a very good prof who is willing to answer any questions from students patiently. He gave us another chance to improve our first midterm grades; When I met tech problems on the second midterm, he finally marked my grades, even he said tech issues do not constitute valid reasons before.
Can sometimes be unclear in his lectures, but he shows great concern for his students and is willing to change his marks given when offered feedback. Overall, a very nice, friendly professor!

Mr. Cebanu was a great math prof and is extremely accommodating. The class average was relatively low, so he decided to make the exam worth 100% of your grade if it was higher than the two midterm's average. Not promising that he'll do so for you, so study! Midterms & exams are difficult, but all the resources you need are given to you.

Amazing guy who tries his best and really cares for his students. His first midterm was hard, but he gave an optional assignment worth half of the first midterm. After the first midterm, he was very fair, and obtaining an 80 in the class is very attainable.

Professor Cebanu is very kind, he gives extra assignments to boost marks and he gives solutions to the questions he posts for homework. His lectures are a bit fast but he posts his notes/recordings so you can look through them again. Overall, very caring towards his students.
Hard, but great lecturer

Do not take any classes with him. Made the midterm extremely hard versus the other profs for this class. Didn't go over the concepts on the test in class, and purposely made it harder because we are forced to take the test at home.

As a parent watching over this as this class is online, I hope the UOttawa is carefully monitoring this prof. Also there are different ways exams are being monitored online for different profs for the same math course. Huge red flag! This prof stated, that he wanted to make the midterm harder. That's fine but at least teach the material.

The midterm was designed to be hard & material was clearly not taught. Apparently, this professor is more worried about his street cred than actually worrying about students. It would be nice if he was concerned about students, the extra stress Covid has placed on them and to give a F about them. Very selfish and uncaring!
GOAT
Amazing prof.
Not very good at explaining the concepts but he clearly cares and wants you to do good. Answers to emails and is very accessible outside of class.

He has a hard time trying to explain concepts but when he shows you the math, its obvious he knows what he's doing and can clearly explain things to you through pen and paper. The midterms were fair and covered each unit thoroughly, although the tests were for every lecture and not just his.

Lecture notes are unorganized and messy. He scribbles notes down on paper to post them later online, which will appear a week later. Gets TAs to poorly mark midterms and assignments. He doesnt write your grade down. When you pick it up from his office he pulls out a mess of papers from a gym bag and then you write your grade in his book.

This dude is so unintentionally funny, hes somewhat awkward but it makes him more likeable. If youve taken MC4VU itll be an easy A. Textbook is pointless to get unless you struggle with calc. Midterms are very easy, he reviews what will be on them the last lecture before them too. Overall great prof.
